Note:
Runa Standard Library: JavaScript Interop Module

This module provides comprehensive JavaScript integration capabilities, enabling seamless
interoperation between Runa and JavaScript code in both browser and Node.js environments.
Features zero-copy data exchange, V8 engine integration, and advanced async/await bridging.

Key Features:
- V8 JavaScript engine integration with isolated contexts
- Zero-copy data exchange with TypedArrays and SharedArrayBuffers
- Bidirectional Promise/async-await bridging
- WebAssembly compilation and execution
- Node.js process and module system integration
- Browser DOM and Web API access
- ES6+ feature support with module systems
- Event loop coordination between JavaScript and Runa
- Real-time debugging and profiling capabilities
- Security sandboxing with CSP and origin policies
- Hot module replacement and live reloading
- JavaScript bundling and optimization pipelines
:End Note

Import "interop/ffi" as FFI
Import "collections/dict" as Dict
Import "collections/list" as List
Import "datetime/time" as Time
Import "uuid" as UUID
Import "errors" as Errors
Import "logging" as Log
Import "async" as Async

Note: JavaScript Runtime Type System
Type JSRuntime is Dictionary with:
    runtime_id as String
    engine_type as JSEngineType
    context_isolates as Dictionary[String, JSContext]
    module_cache as Dictionary[String, JSModule]
    promise_bridge as JSPromiseBridge
    event_loop as JSEventLoop
    memory_allocator as JSMemoryAllocator
    debugger as JSDebugger
    profiler as JSProfiler
    security_manager as JSSecurityManager
    bundler as JSBundler
    optimizer as JSOptimizer
    wasm_compiler as JSWasmCompiler
    hot_reload_manager as JSHotReloadManager

